extendedInfo.description: The freedom of mobile banking is here! At Defence Bank we pride ourselves on service, support & financial security. As a part of continuing to improve our service you can now access banking wherever you are, through our Defence Bank App. It lets you: - Find Branch and ATM locations near you - Stay up to date with news, events and promotions - and gives you convenient access to Mobile Banking to: - Check account balances - Transfer money to other accounts - Pay bills via BPAY - View recent transactions - View your Auto Transfers. To use Mobile Banking, you must first be registered for Defence Bank Online Banking. If you are not registered yet, then follow the instructions below. - Login to Defence Bank Online Banking via our Web Page (www.defencebank.com.au) - Click on the "Maintenance" tab, at the top right hand corner of the screen - From the menu on the left hand side, click "Contact Details". - Ensure the mobile phone number recorded is your current mobile phone number. - Click "Save Details". - From the menu on the left hand side, click "Mobile Preferences". - Read the amendments to Defence Bank's Products and Services Conditions of Use. - Check the checkbox beside each account that you would like to access via Mobile Banking. - Click "Save my Mobile Banking Preferences". - You are now registered for Defence Bank Mobile Banking! We hope you enjoy the convenience of being able to stay on top of your banking, wherever you are in the world, from the convenience of your smartphone.

reviews.title: Update fixed everything :-)
reviews.comment: Before it wasn\'t allowing login, now everything works great. So much easier then using a web browser. Recommended for everyone with defence bank.
reviews.author: Russ T

reviews.title: BETTER THIS TIME
reviews.comment: Good app,better than embarrassing first app. Can you tweak so numbers auto present for member naumber?
reviews.author: Mick Welsh

reviews.title: Works well.
reviews.comment: No more chasing the keyboard around the screen! This app is really handy, much better than using an internet browser on windows or android.
reviews.author: Roger Symons

reviews.title: Handy
reviews.comment: Much happier now that it works.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Slow and buggy
reviews.comment: Loading between screens still slow. There is no balace of your account in the transaction history view. Can we please have more than two pages of transaction history? oh and an idea if the app is loading/working (a spinning wheel, hourglass etc) would be usefull too. This app still needs a more work, but is getting better.
reviews.author: Nathan Bradford

reviews.title: Rubbish
reviews.comment: Just a web browser
reviews.author: Mick Sander

reviews.title: Functionality ok, graphics buggy
reviews.comment: I found that most of the basic functionality was there but the screens were sometimes too big for my phone or the graphics were examples of poor UI design. Good enough as a start.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Can\'t use!
reviews.comment: I\'ve been looking forward to having an easy to use app to do my banking with, though this does not met my expectations. I can\'t even type my member number in. Why do apps get released when they don\'t work?!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Needs a lot of work
reviews.comment: I installed original directly from bank before this app was released. The original app works reasonably well but this app is far from ready. eg: when the back button is pushed to exit the keyboard the app exits instead. Very unuser friendly.
reviews.author: Rod Oldfella

reviews.title: Convenient
reviews.comment: Simple to log in, make transfers, check balance and transaction, interest and make BPAY pmts. Shows you nearest atms and specials as well as contact points. Could be a bit more user friendly but worth downloading and much easier on your phone.
reviews.author: Jason Hunt

reviews.title: Horrible
reviews.comment: Android 4.2. Screen disappears as keyboard appears, details don\'t enter, can\'t login. Just horrible. And browser access doesn\'t work either of course meaning I\'m stuck in the dark ages of no mobile banking capability
reviews.author: Andre Camenzind

reviews.title: Terrible App
reviews.comment: Still doesn\'t even look legit yet, still made by Komosion. Terrible! Slow as hell, if you accidentally click the wrong button, you need to re-login. I only use it to check balances, but I am sure there is more bugs I am yet to find.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Can\'t input acc or password
reviews.comment: The only way to login atm is to cut and paste your details... It sort of works once logged in but I\'d give it a miss until it\'s had a few more updates applied.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Needs refinement
reviews.comment: Clunky and slow. Needs to be refined. The can is digits and yet automatically opens to the letters.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Not ready for release...  Or scam?
reviews.comment: Can\'t login.  Blocking issue.  What developer would put their own name to an app like this.   Additionally, it\'s important for a banking app to be published correctly. Publish it as defBank or something so it doesn\'t look like a scam.  Komosian... Not sure I even WANT to login. Not good for Komosian. Not good for defence bank. Maybe this is acceptable in iPhone world.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: Works for me
reviews.comment: App works fine for my S3 with its simplicity in design a great relief compared to other banking apps. Not as secure as internet site but good overall.
reviews.author: James W

reviews.title: Alright but could use some work
reviews.comment: I am unable to see credits to my account would be good If I could see what is going into my account as well as out going.
reviews.author: Runesmisstress Hamilton

reviews.title: Worst banking App
reviews.comment: I run Android 4.2 and it doesn\'t allow me to log on. It\'s very buggy.VERY POOR APP! Defence Bank should create a HTML 5 website instead of creating a phone app. Kudos for trying!
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: A bit lumpy
reviews.comment: I found this a bit clunky compared to other apps.  I have stopped using it and gone back to my laptop. If an update was released, I would try it again.
reviews.author: MH Phelan

reviews.title: Cannot log in
reviews.comment: The app will not let me type anything in the password or member number!
reviews.author: Hayden Lewis
